metatags.og:title: Colorado Attorney General Settles Data Breach Investigation with Broomfield Skilled Nursing and Rehabilitation Center
metatags.og:description: A settlement has been reached between the Colorado Attorney General and Broomfield Skilled Nursing and Rehabilitation Center that resolves alleged The Colorado attorney general investigated a 2021 data breach at Broomfield Skilled Nursing and Rehabilitation Center and determined HIPAA and state data protection laws had been violated. A financial penalty of $60,000 was imposed, $25,000 of which will be suspended if there is full compliance with the settlement agreement.
